<TEXT>
playwright richard foreman actor christopher 
reeve and director peter brook were among 24 people recognized 
monday night for their contribution to off and offoff broadway 
theater at the 33rd annual village voice obie awards ceremony 
foreman was honored with an obie for sustained achievement as a 
playwright sharing the award for best new play were caryl 
churchill for serious money and maria irene fornes for 
abingdon square 
the playwrights awards included 1000 in cash grants from the 
voice 
george bartenieff and roberts blossom won obies for sustained 
excellence in performance reeve was honored for his courageous 
work on behalf of chilean artists 
actress kathleen turner and actor eric bogosian presided over 
the awards ceremony at the ritz in greenwich village 
receiving obies in the performance category were larry bazzell 
for the signal season of dummy hoy kathy bates for frankie amp 
johnny in the claire de lune yvonne bryceland for the road to 
mecca victor garber for wenceslas square and erland 
josephson for the cherry orchard 
also gordana rashovich for a shayna maidel john seitz for 
abingdon square peggy shaw for dress suits to hire tina 
shepard for the three lives of lucie cabrol and lauren tom for 
american notes 
obies in the director category went to anne bogart for no 
plays no poetry brook for the mahabharata and julie 
taymor for juan darien 
eva buchmuller was honored for sustained excellence in stage 
design huck snyder for sustained excellence in scenic design and 
bh barry for sustained excellence in combat choreography 
elliot goldenthal won an obie for his music in juan darien 
also honored were the csc repertory company and the theatre for 
a new audience which received 5000 cash grants from the 
newspaper for achieving artistic excellence while working with 
severe budget limitations 
village voice critics judged the 1988 obies for off and offoff 
broadway guest judges were clinton davis of the nontraditional 
casting project and judith malina founder and artistic director 
of the living theatre 
