<TEXT>
a record 65000 people walked across the 
43 mile eastbound span of the chesapeake bay bridge 
stollers were met sunday on the west side by gov william donald 
schaefer who kicked off his one million marylanders bay cleanup 
campaign an attempt to get residents to practice water 
conservation and change household disposal habits 
the bay bridge walk which began at 9 am and was completed by 
530 pm drew 15000 more people this year than last years 
record in part because sunday was one of the first warm weekend 
days in what has been a rainy cool spring 
the first annual walk was in 1975 
im out here every year because its here said st marys 
resident james chesley why you walk across a bridge is the same 
reason you climb a mountain because its there 
 
</TEXT>
