on the other hand you run into this kind of block with no 
explanation on certain issues as to why once you are there in 
these places you cant do certain things the security people can 
override everybody else and they dont feel a need to explain 
the reason 
hooley said the initial preparations for the summit consisted 
mainly of checking with people who had been involved in moscow 
visits before including some members of the nixon administration 
more active preparations began after the two superpower leaders 
met in washington in december and announced that reagan would visit 
moscow sometime in the spring 
over a period of approximately two months leading up to the 
summit three advance teams visited moscow one more than usual 
for a domestic trip as when the president goes to chicago or 
new london conn one person from the advance offices makes the 
initial survey checking out proposed speech sites with an eye to 
establishing communications security and the other facilities 
needed for a presidential visit 
on a foreign trip this group is increased to about 10 or l2 
senior people who get a few concepts agreed to in consultation 
with their counterparts from the host country hooley said 
the final advance team whether the president is going to 
baltimore or bali is a larger group of maybe 45 to 50 including 
technical people to make specific arrangements 
