some of the 4700 firestone inc employees in 
six states who had been on strike returned to work late sunday 
after negotiators reached tentative agreement with the united 
rubber workers on a new contract 
union spokesman curt brown said ratification votes on the 
threeyear contract would be held this week at firestone offices 
and plants in akron noblesville ind des moines iowa decatur 
ill russellville ark and oklahoma city 
workers at decatur russellville and nobelsville plants started 
to return to work sunday night workers in akron were expected to 
be back on the job tuesday morning 
the urw members struck may 15 after firestone declined to accept 
the costofliving allowance provided in an industry pattern 
agreement the union negotiated with goodyear tire amp rubber co 
brown said the new contract followed the goodyear pattern 
reached may 17 
our major goal had been to keep pattern bargaining and that 
had been all we really asked from firestone brown said this 
isnt really a greedy contract 
firestone spokesman robert troyer said we believe this is a 
fair and realistic contract for our employees the agreement 
recognizes the particular needs of firestones tire operation 
he said the company was optimistic for early ratification of the 
contract 
under the agreement firestone would 
maintain costofliving allowances in each year with a 
onecent hourly increase for every increase of 026 in the consumer 
price index 
boost wages 25 cents per hour by deducting that amount from 
future costofliving adjustments in increments of 10 10 and 5 
cents 
increase retirement pensions for current workers by 350 to 
2350 per month for each year of service in addition current 
retirees would receive a lump sum bonus of 200 before dec 1 
provide choice of firstdollar health insurance coverage or an 
8020 percent copayment plan that includes a 1000 enrollment 
incentive bonus 
make 35 percent matching contributions in the employee savings 
plan that is part of the 8020 comprehensive health plan both 
plans provide for a 401k savings plan 
in addition the pact assures continuation of the contract if a 
firestone plant is sold to another company during the next three 
years and contains a nostrike wage reopener clause in the third 
year 
negotiations resumed saturday at 115 pm with the assistance 
of federal mediator david thorley and an agreement was reached at 5 
am it was the only session held since the strike began may 15 
the strike was the first involving firestone since 1976 when 
the urw struck all the akronbased rubber companies except general 
tire 
