institute said the strongest quakes two occurring sunday 
afternoon registered 44 on the richter scale some local radio 
stations reported the sunday quakes caused cracks in some houses 
and broken windows in the downtown commercial area 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph a quake with a magnitude of 4 can cause moderate 
damage 
the seismological service measured 22 quakes on saturday with 
the strongest registering 4 on the richter scale 
the epicenter of the quakes was on the southwestern edge of the 
capital near la aurora international airport said sanchez on 
thursday a quake registering 4 on the richter scale was felt in 
the area 
a quake measuring 7 on the richter scale devastated the capital 
on feb 4 1976 causing more than 22000 deaths 
