mussolinis last government and the founder of italys neofascist 
party has died at the age of 73 
almirante died sunday of complications from ischemia a 
condition caused by arterial blockage according to hospital 
officials quoted by the italian news agency ansa he had suffered 
from heart disease for years ansa said 
almirante was elected to the the chamber of deputies 11 times 
from 1948 to 1987 he was once charged with helping a rightwing 
terrorist but the charges were dropped under a 1987 amnesty 
his italian social movement was the political heir to 
mussolinis fascist creation by 1987 it had had become italys 
fourthlargest party in parliament holding 59 percent of the 
seats in the chamber of deputies 
another former party leader and founder pino romualdi died of 
cancer friday the 77yearold editor of the party newspaper was 
elected to the chamber of deputies seven times between 1953 and 
1979 and was a senator from 1983 to 1987 
the party announced a joint funeral for the almirante and 
romualdi tuesday at st agnes the roman catholic church in romes 
piazza navona 
almirante born june 27 1914 joined mussolinis last 
government in 1943 as chief of staff of the ministry of popular 
culture he served until mussolinis fall in 1945 
mussolini who came to power in 1922 was shot and hanged in a 
public square in milan in april 1945 
in february 1979 the chamber of deputies waived almirantes 
parliamentary immunity so prosecutors could try him for reviving 
the political equivalent of the outlawed fascist party but he was 
reelected to parliament and the immunitylifting process had to 
begin again 
he never went to trial 
parliament waived his immunity again in 1981 and in 1984 so he 
could face charges of aiding and abetting a rightwing terrorist 
accused in a 1972 bombing that killed two italian policemen 
almirante was accused of helping finance a surgical operation to 
change the vocal cords of a bombing suspect to dodge his 
identification by voice patterns 
those charges were dropped under a february 1987 amnesty that 
covered offenses that would bring less than three years punishment 
in december almirante stepped down as national secretary of the 
neofascist party which supports a halt to the influx of foreign 
immigrants into italy a stronger presidency and tougher measures 
against organized crime 
he is survived by his wife rafaela and their four children 
