<TEXT>
dino grandi who lost out to benito mussolini in a 
1921 bid for leadership of the fascist party and helped depose the 
dictator in 1943 has died at the age of 92 
grandi died at his home in bologna on saturday the staterun 
raitv said he had reportedly been suffering cardiac and 
circulatory problems 
grandi fought in world war i and joined the fascist squads that 
terrorized the italian countryside he failed to win the leadership 
of the fascists at a national congress in 1921 but successfully 
made a bid for a seat in parliament 
he participated in the october 1922 march on rome that led to 
mussolinis installation as head of government grandi served as 
undersecretary of the interior in 1924 and was foreign minister 
from 1929 to 1934 
grandi clashed with mussolini urging him to support britain and 
not germany in world war ii and opposing italys active 
participation in the campaign he urged king victor emmanuel iii to 
remove mussolini from government 
in july 1943 grandi presented the government resolution that 
deposed mussolini mussolini later headed a puppet government 
supported by the german nazis in northern italy until he was 
captured and hanged by italian partisans in april 1945 
a fascist tribunal in 1944 condemned grandi to death but he had 
escaped to lisbon and went on to brazil 
no funeral plans were announced 
news of grandis death came a day before the funeral of giorgio 
almirante who had a minor role in mussolini government and who for 
years led italys small but fourthlargest party the neofascist 
italian social movement 
another neofascist figure pino romualdi died last week there 
will be a joint funeral for almirante and romualdi in rome on 
tuesday 
