power when asked about the system for selecting the 5000 delegates 
to the conference 
the fact that the party delegates are selected by the party 
machinery by the party committees effects the procedure and not 
in every case can it be called a democratic effect she said 
it was not clear whether she was advocating extension of the 
delegate selection into nonparty groups or criticizing some of the 
officials chosen 
