representative in china working on getting the documents to the 
service 
zoo spokeswoman patty napierala confirmed that the zoo had 
gotten the green light to open the exhibit and plans to do so at 
noon tuesday 
the zoo has spent nearly 3 million in preparing to exhibit the 
pandas as part of toledos 150th anniversary celebration 
in a bid to stop the exhibit the world wildlife fund filed suit 
against the wildlife service arguing that the exhibit would 
violate an international convention that bars trafficking in 
endangered species for commercial purposes 
klinger said toledo zoo officials had sought unsuccessfully to 
be exempted from the convention on endangered species and had filed 
an exemption form with the service instead of the full export 
permit as required 
when the pandas arrived in chicago on may 13 the paperwork had 
not been corrected klinger said the service decided it would be 
best for the pandas to allow them to go on to toledo and to take up 
the issue later 
</TEXT>
