<TEXT>
jesse jackson unveiled a fiveyear 
budget plan that would raise taxes on the rich freeze defense 
spending and increase support for social programs on monday he 
dismissed democratic rival michael dukakis earlier proposals as 
radically conservative 
dukakis the democratic presidential frontrunner defended his 
spending priorities saying they do represent a fundamental 
change 
and he indirectly criticized jackson for trying to map out 
specific expenses so far in advance theres no way you can 
prepare a budget today for 1989 dukakis said after an appearance 
at a child care center in cranford nj 
the massachusetts governor spent most of monday in boston while 
george bush was in washington leaving the campaign trail to 
jackson 
jackson made sure they werent forgotten attacking the budget 
policies of the reagan administration and complaining that dukakis 
proposed changes were too timid 
we cannot be fooled into thinking the reaganbush deficits 
make social justice impossible jackson said at a news 
conference the jackson budget reduces the deficit and funds 
needed investments this is a budget for a strong and secure 
america 
jackson also made an appearance at a day care center and the 
rancho seco nuclear power plant the object of a sacramento area 
voters referendum seeking to shut it down permanently as he 
campaigned for his share of the 314 democratic national convention 
delegates up for grabs in californias june 7 presidential primary 
jackson drew some boos from the rancho seco plant workers when 
he told them the nuclear power industry is a dangerous job 
option 
his fiveyear federal budget plan would increase taxes on the 
wealthy by 244 billion and on corporations by 104 billion cut 
defense spending by 164 billion by imposing a fiveyear freeze on 
projected spending hikes and increase spending on social programs 
by 344 billion 
he said it would also cut the nations deficit from a projected 
134 billion in 1993 to 49 billion 
jackson repeatedly contrasted his budget proposals with those of 
dukakis which he characterized as inadequate to reverse the 
republican priorities set over the past eight years by president 
reagan 
reagan has cut investment in health care housing legal 
services day care scholarships by more than 100 billion mr 
dukakis rails against that as being wrong but offers to offset it 
by only 775 million jackson said 
that is radically conservative away from the dreams and 
aspirations of most democrats unless there is a commitment to 
economic justice and change he will find himself taken adrift to 
sea by the democratic constituents instead of leading them he 
will be on a raft without a rudder jackson said of dukakis 
our commitment is not to make bland beautiful its new 
directions jackson continued 
christopher edley dukakis issues director said jackson was 
unfairly criticizing dukakis plans for spending 775 million 
500 million on the fund to rebuild america 250 million on a 
teacher excellence program and 25 million on a literacy corps 
the way to make critical new investments in a time of 
tripledigit deficits is not to make unrealistic promises about 
massive new spending edley said in a telephone interview from 
boston we have to think of creative ways to use modest federal 
resources to pull in private and state and local funds 
jackson repeating a campaign theme said he would raise up to 
58 billion a year for social programs such as housing education 
and health care by freezing the military budget at its current 300 
billion level for the next five years 
my plan allows for a significant new social investment 
including doubling of the education budget by 1993 a new national 
housing initiative and an additional 3 billion per year for the 
war on drugs these investments and deficit reduction are made 
possible by a combination of fair taxes on the wealthy and 
corporations and a freeze on pentagon spending for five years 
jackson said 
i am for a strong defense i also support a sound approach to 
the military budget our plan would freeze military spending 
jackson said 
cost overruns two additional aircraft carrier task forces 
star wars and the midgetman do not make us stronger they undermine 
our economy and make us weaker even after the jackson cuts real 
military spending will be 25 percent higher in 1993 than in 1980 
he said 
dukakis also opposes the two additional aircraft carrier task 
forces and the midgetman missile system and would cut back the 
star wars nuclear defense program to 1983 levels dukakis has 
called for a stable overall defense budget with increases in 
conventional forces coming from cuts in strategic systems 
the biggest tax increase in jacksons budget plan would restore 
the top 385 percent income tax rate its just the top 600000 
taxpayers who earn 200000 and above who will return from 28 
percent to 385 percent they can afford it jackson said 
other revenue measures would increase the minimum tax rate on 
corporations impose a 05 percent securities transfer excise tax 
to raise 10 billion annual revenue and discourage major corporate 
mergers and takeovers limit deductions for business meals to 50 
percent and impose a 7billionayear polluters tax on 
corporations 
among his proposed new investments are programs which by 
1993 would spend an extra 20 billion annually on education and job 
training 17 billion on housing programs 12 billion on health 
and nutrition programs and 3 billion more annually on aids 
programs 
jacksons budget proposals also include 5 billion more in 
transportation funding 45 billion for scientific research in 
nonmilitary fields 17 billion annually on environmental 
programs and 1 billion more annually for international economic 
assistance 
