<TEXT>
the supreme court heard an appeal monday by an 
arabamerican advocate of civil disobedience who asked the judges 
to revoke a deportation order against him 
he threatened to convert to judaism and return to israel if the 
order stands 
mubarak awad 44 was ordered deported by israeli officials on 
may 6 they said he had played a leading role in the 24week arab 
uprising in the occupied west bank and gaza strip 
the threejudge panel reserved decision after mondays appeal 
hearing but did not set a date for its ruling the decision is 
expected to have farreaching consequences for the legal status of 
the 130000 arabs living in israeliannexed east jerusalem 
during the threehour hearing lawyers for both sides focused on 
awads legal status under israeli immigration law 
the court must consider whether the jerusalemborn awad and 
other east jerusalem arabs enjoy an irrevocable status as permanent 
residents or if they can lose their rights under certain 
conditions such as leaving the country for more than seven years 
nili arad an attorney for the interior ministry argued that 
awad should be deported because he forfeited his right to permanent 
residency by leaving israel for 13 years from 1970 to 1983 and by 
accepting us citizenship awad lived in wapakoneta ohio while 
maintaining a home in jerusalem 
awads attorney avraham gal said israel had no right to deport 
his client because as a longtime resident of arab east jerusalem 
awad enjoys a special status that cannot be revoked 
israel annexed east jerusalem after the 1967 middle east war 
but never defined the legal status of the sectors arab residents 
most of whom rejected offers of israeli citizenship 
ms arad argued that since the annexation the interior ministry 
in practice has applied the rules of permanent residency to 
citizens of east jerusalem and that awad falls into that category 
if the court rules in favor of the interior ministry all east 
jerusalemites are in danger of mass transfer said jonathan 
kuttab a west bank lawyer also representing the arabamerican 
those who grant residency permits can also take them away 
he added 
awad who has been jailed since may 5 looked pale when he 
