ice cream entrepreneur charles 
sandford didnt believe vanilla and chocolate were enough to draw 
in customers so he added such flavors as fire flying fish and 
sex 
sex is the most exotic the 37yearold sandford said asked 
whats in it he replies large ripe juicy barbados cherries 
that simmer in crystalclear champagne until they pop 
sandfords recipe for the flying fish flavor includes fish mash 
and smooth peanut butter as well as milk eggs and butter the 
flying fish is the national symbol of barbados a former british 
colony 
i just invented a new flavor to commemorate the islands 21st 
anniversary of independence sandford said the concoction 
includes 21 different kinds of fruit and is called appropriately 
enough the 21 it tastes like a very rich punch 
sandford grew up in new york city where he studied to be a 
clothes designer he ran his own small store until his 
barbadosborn wife judy suggested eight years ago that an ice 
cream shop in her prosperous and hot caribbean island might be more 
fun and profitable 
sandford sold his business in new york and went to milan where 
he served an apprenticeship at fragole fabri one of italys 
biggest ice cream factories 
i learned the basics just enough to make vanilla ice cream 
he said after the first six months i knew how to make ice 
cream but i had to learn to improve it and then to master it 
today he said i am the king 
sandford makes 18 flavors fresh each day he claims he has 
created 751 in all and is seeking an entry in the guinness book of 
records 
every single recipe is different he said i do not take a 
vanilla base and simpl change the name as i add different 
ingredients 
sandford also meets special requests 
on wednesdays he prepares ice cream for diabetics using 
artificial sweeteners instead of sugar 
for vegetarians sandford makes carrot and zucchini ice cream 
creamy avocado also is popular 
not every flavor is a bestseller 
tomato did not do too well he said too acidic 
some flavors contain promotional gimmicks the main ingredient 
in money ice cream is a tightlyrolled barbados dollar wrapped 
in plastic 
