a federal judge monday cleared the way 
for swedens ab electrolux to pursue its 182 million hostile bid 
for murray ohio manufacturing co a maker of lawn mowers and 
bicycles 
electrolux announced immediately that it would increase its bid 
to 197 million upping the tender offer from 48 to 52 per share 
of murray ohio common stock electrolux said the tender offer would 
be subject to shareholder approval only if ab electrolux is not 
satisfied that the ohio control share act is inapplicable to the 
offer 
the ohio control share act is an antitakeover law and the 
electrolux statement said it would seek a ruling from federal 
courts in ohio that the act is inapplicable 
us district judge thomas a wiseman dissolved a temporary 
injunction against electroluxs 48ashare offer by discounting 
murray ohios allegations that a new york law firm which once 
represented the tennessee company passed confidential information 
to electrolux 
the firm sullivan amp cromwell had advised murray ohio on how to 
defend itself against takeovers before it represented electrolux in 
its tender offer 
hans g backman executive vice president of the stockholmbased 
appliance maker had testified last week that electrolux received 
no confidential information directly or indirectly from sullivan amp 
cromwell 
he said his company based its action on murray ohios annual 
stockholders report as well as other public documents 
all the information appeared in an magazine article that was 
readily available to any professional investigator wiseman 
agreed in his ruling 
electrolux also said monday it has no plans to move murray ohio 
operations from the present plant at lawrenceburg tenn 
