<TEXT>
the federal trade commission said monday it 
would seek a preliminary injunction to block mccormick amp co incs 
proposed 56 million acquisition of specialty brands inc on 
grounds the merger may be anticompetitive 
the ftc authorized its staff to seek the injunction saying the 
acquisition could substantially reduce competition in the 
production and sale of spices 
ftc spokeswoman susan ticknor said the commission voting 40 
authorized its staff to ask a federal district court to block the 
acquisition pending administrative proceedings to determine the 
legality of the takeover 
us district court judge john h pratt on april 26 had 
temporarily enjoined the merger at the ftcs request while the ftc 
sought additional documents from mccormick to determine if the 
merger would be anticompetitive 
mccormick based in hunt valley md is the worlds largest 
spice producer san franciscobased specialty brands makes spice 
islands gourmet spices and is owned by ub foods us inc a 
holding company for the us interests of united biscuits 
holdings plc a major british company 
specialty recently sold its salad dressing and olive business to 
campbell soup co mccormick was seeking to buy specialtys spice 
islands and taste of americana gourmet operations 
a spokesman for specialty brands said the company had no 
comment spokesmen for mccormick could not be reached for comment 
monday night 
mccormick said earlier this month it had reached an agreement 
with the ftc to allow it to proceed with its bid 
mccormick said at the time that legal obstacles preventing it 
from acquiring spice islands had been lifted under an agreement 
with the ftc 
